# Brand Marketplace — Master Specification

**Version:** 1.0
**Owner:** Jason Wineti (Ngāi Tahu)
**Status:** Patent-Ready | Part of the Unified Platform

---

## 1. Overview

The Brand Marketplace is the commercial layer of the Unified Platform. It enables QSR, retail, sports, FMCG, and entertainment brands to sell digital goods, run gamified challenges, activate reward boosts, build loyalty, and collaborate with creators — all within a youth-safe, identity-verified environment. No personal data is ever shared.

---

## 2. Core Features

### Brand Storefronts
Verified brands receive customisable storefronts to sell digital cosmetics, game content, lore packs, and experience tickets. All purchases transact in BRICK KOIN or fiat via the internal bridge. Storefront visibility is earned through community rating and Brick Reputation, not paid promotion.

### Brand Questlines
Multi-step, gamified brand campaigns that reward users with BRICKS and exclusive digital badges. Each questline contains 3–10 tasks spanning creative, gameplay, and hybrid physical-digital challenges. Questlines plug directly into the AI Workforce V2 task engine.

### Brand Season Passes
30-day themed content drops including exclusive cosmetics, limited challenges, seasonal boosts, event access, and brand lore. Paid in BRICKS. Not a subscription — a one-time digital purchase with progressive unlock.

### Brand Loyalty Tiers
Kids earn Brand XP by interacting with a brand. Four tiers: Bronze (3 interactions), Silver (10), Gold (25), Diamond (50). Rewards include exclusive cosmetics, bonus BRICK tasks, early access to new items, and special Shed event invitations. Not a financial loyalty programme — a creative engagement ladder.

### Brand Boosts
Time-limited reward multipliers purchased by brands. 1.5× or 2× boosts applied to gameplay tasks, creative tasks, and hybrid physical-digital events. Brands pre-load a boost wallet with BRICKS. The system deducts automatically.

### Brand Drop Days
Weekly Friday releases of new cosmetics, challenges, boosts, and lore packs. Creates predictable engagement cycles and marketplace traffic.

### Brand Collabs
Two or more brands co-create themed cosmetics, hybrid challenges, Shed events, and seasonal passes. Revenue splits configured automatically. Collaboration history and performance metrics tracked.

### Brand-to-Creator Collabs
Brands hire verified creators (16+) to produce custom cosmetics, lore, mini-games, and challenge packs. BRICKS held in escrow until delivery approved. Creator ratings and portfolio visible in the Creator Directory.

